{
  "name": "ToolEQA on HM-EQA",
  "description": "ToolEQA (Zhai et al., arXiv 2510.20310, ICLR 2026 in review) — tool-augmented active explorer for HM-EQA. Each iter is one ReAct step: build prompt from prior Thought/Code/Observation transcript, call Qwen2.5-VL with current rgb, parse code, exec via transformers.agents.python_interpreter.evaluate_python_code with 6 tools (VisualQA / ObjectLocation2D / ObjectLocation3D / ObjectCrop / GoNextPointTool / final_answer; SegmentInstance is dead in upstream's active toolbox). Discrete GoNextPointTool commands (move_forward 0.5m / turn_left 45° / turn_right 45° / turn_around 180°) are translated to free-pose JSON for env_hmeqa__step. Read tools call env_detany3d (server-mode, DetAny3D + GroundingDINO + SAM). PortBench v1 target (zero-shot vs paper Table 5: 62.3% SR / 18.26m).",
